The Cinderteeth Mountains (Thrak-Essen) erupted after generations of ignored warning signs.
The Ashfall Monsoon sent black rain across Kowloon's delta for months, drowning crops under ash-laden water.

The Salt Ledger Kingdoms collapsed. Caravan routes became impassable.
Cistern infrastructure failed as ash contaminated water supplies across the eastern desert.

The Ashfall drove formation of the Spirebound Conclave, chartered to preserve dangerous knowledge from institutional collapse.
The same volcanic instability that powered the Conclave's geothermal forges eventually destroyed it during a seismic event.

In Kowloon's delta, the Ashfall triggered the Neon Covenant: one ledger, one ration code, one law.
The Covenant was survival arithmetic, not idealism.

The Ashfall created the Ashborn race: peoples marked by generations of volcanic exposure whose bodies carry trace elements of the eruption.
The Cinderteeth still vent. Scholars warn the same forces are building toward another release.
